OL,3,CWelsh Government to announce spending
OL,4,Cplans for next financial year
OL,6,FThe Conservatives are again unlikely
OL,7,Fto back the plans and all the
OL,8,Findications are that a deal couldn't
OL,9,Fbe agreed with Plaid Cymru. There's
OL,10,Fnow one Reform UK member, the former
OL,11,FConservative, Laura-Anne Jones.
OL,13,FIf Labour can't win enough support by
OL,14,Fthe time of the final vote in January,
OL,15,Fa law kicks in meaning that only 75%
OL,16,Fof the budget can be spent. That will
OL,17,Fmean cuts for services, which could
OL,18,Ffall most heavily on local councils.
